related_questions.question: What is the real name of pizza?
related_questions.answer: A precursor of pizza was probably the focaccia, a flat bread known to the Romans as panis focacius, to which toppings were then added. Modern pizza evolved from similar flatbread dishes in Naples, Italy, in the 18th or early 19th century.

inline_videos.title: How To Grow Tomatoes At Home (SEED TO HARVEST)

key_moments.text: Take some fresh Tomatoes (Prefer Heirloom varieties) Cut them into slices
Seeds can be sown from September to October
With a help of a gardening tool take the plants out from the seedling pot. Make sure not to disturb the roots during the transplanting process
RIGHT WAY TO PLANT: Tomatoes must be planted deeply. Deep planting encourages healthy and strong root system. At the time of planting, cover bottom 2/3 part of the plant with potting soil.
LOCATION:Your tomato plants need between 4-6 hours of total sun per day in order to grow and eventually produce fruit.
POLLINATION: While tomato flowers are typically pollinated y wind, and occasionally by bees, the lack of air movement or low insect numbers can slow down the natural pollination process
FERTILIZER: You can fertilize the plants with fishmeal, chicken manure,vermi compost or any other organic fertilizer.
Too much water and your plant's roots will rot. Too little water and your plants will get weak.
As the tomatoes grow bigger and heavier provide extra support to the stems
Ripe tomatoes can be plucked by gently pulling at the stem with your fingers. Or, use a sharp scissor to snip them off their branches
